.TH "fm10k_update_uc_addr_vf" 9 "fm10k_update_uc_addr_vf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_update_uc_addr_vf \- Update device unicast addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_update_uc_addr_vf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 __always_unused glort "  ","
.BI "const u8 *mac "  ","
.BI "u16 vid "  ","
.BI "bool add "  ","
.BI "u8 __always_unused flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "glort" 12
unused
.IP "mac" 12
MAC address to add/remove from table
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN ID to add/remove from table
.IP "add" 12
Indicates if this is an add or remove operation
.IP "flags" 12
flags field to indicate add and secure - unused

This function is used to add or remove unicast MAC addresses for
the VF.
